sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_upvotes
FROM post_votes
WHERE vote_type = 'upvote';

SELECT AVG(comment_count) AS average_reports_per_comment
FROM (
  SELECT comment_id, COUNT(*) AS comment_count
  FROM comment_reports
  GROUP BY comment_id
);

external_knowledge:
- "torchbearers" refers to active moderators; 
- "left their mark on the community" means they have edited either posts or comments; 
- "holding the flame" means they are still active (is_active = 1).

sql:
SELECT post_id, SUM(comment_count) AS total_comments, SUM(upvote_count) AS total_upvotes
FROM post_analytics
GROUP BY post_id;

external_knowledge:
Being an active moderator means the moderator's is_active flag is set to 1; 
Total activity refers to the total count of user activities; 
Average activity is calculated across all users' activities.

sql:
SELECT 
    (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT post_id) FROM post_votes) + 
    (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT comment_id) FROM comment_votes) AS total_votes;

SELECT comment_id, MAX(edited_at) AS last_edit_time
FROM comment_history
GROUP BY comment_id;

SELECT post_id, upvote_count
FROM post_analytics
WHERE upvote_count = (SELECT MAX(upvote_count) FROM post_analytics);
